					<section>
						<h2>Version Control</h2>
						<h3>github</h3>
						<p>Using a local version control system is a given, but also push code to a VCS in the cloud, and use API webhooks to integrate with other cloud services.</p>
						<p><i>Alternatives are Bitbucket, Gitlab, or even Launchpad.</i></p>
						<aside class="notes" data-markdown>
							* Webhooks.
							* Service integrations.
							* Code changes trigger *EVERYTHING*
						</aside>
					</section>
					<section>
						<h2>Automatic Testing</h2>
						<h3>Travis-CI</h3>
						<p>Whenever changes are pushed to github, Travis-CI will checkout a copy of the code,
							build it, and execute tests.</p>
						<p>The build process should also trigger a deployment to test and production servers.</p>
						<p><i>Alternatives are Jenkins or Bamboo</i></p>
						<aside class="notes" data-markdown>
							* Code coverage with Coveralls service.
							* Check in python shell, then make it a test.
						</aside>
					</section>
					<section>
						<h2>Tracking new features</h2>
						<h3>Pivotal Tracker</h3>
						<p>A tool to track new features and estimate when they can be completed.</p>
						<p>Ideally the tool should link to the VCS and record what code implemented a feature.</p>
						<p><i>Alternatives are Jira, Trac, Basecamp, or Stick-It notes.</i></p>
						<aside class="notes" data-markdown>
							* Instead of also tracking bugs in Pivotal, I choose to use github's issue tracker for
							bugs.
							* git hooks to add story id from branch name into commit messages
						</aside>
					</section>
					<section>
						<h2>Group chat</h2>
						<h3>Slack</h3>
						<p>For a team of developers, somewhere to ask questions, hold meetings, share documents and internet memes</p>
						<p>Also useful as a place for notifcations from github and travis-ci</p>
						<p><i>Alternatives are Hipchat, Campfire, perhaps email or an XMPP client&hellip;</i></p>
						<aside class="notes" data-markdown>
							Service will notify once deployement is complete.
						</aside>
					</section>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Cut to - Setting up</h2>
					<p>Let's setup the github repository, and connect it to Travis-CI, Slack, and Pivotal Tracker.</p>
					<aside class="notes" data-markdown>
						* create github repo
						* clone repo locally
						* eclipse settings .project .pydevproject
						* virtualenv
						 * mkvirtualenv mymovie
						 * .venv (override the cd command)
						* requirements.txt
						 * django
						 * django-rest-framework
						* pip install -r requirements.txt
						* django-admin startproject mymovie - then rearrange up one directory
						* make a test
						 * simple import of settings to prove app can start
						 * ./manage.py test
						 * git push
						* travic-ci
						 * add github repo from travis
						* slack
						 * add notification.slack to config
						* pivotal-tracker
						 * add service and API token from tracker
						 * add project, make epics and stories
						 * git hooks prepare-commit-msg to add story id to commit based on branch "my-feature-branch-12345678"
						* coverage with coveralls
						 * add repo at coveralls
						 * update travis conf
					</aside>
				</section>

